<HEAD>Man Gunned Down While Walking</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 22-year-old man was shot to death in a
confrontation with rival gang members as he walked down a street,
authorities said.
   After Theron Shakir was approached by two young men Sunday
evening, words were exchanged and one of them pulled a gun and shot
Shakir twice in the chest, said sheriff's Deputy Hal Grant.
   The suspects fled and Shakir, believed to be a gang member, was
dead on arrival at a hospital, officials said.
   No arrests had been made, Grant said.
   More than 120 people have been killed in gang-related violence
in Los Angeles County this year. The city Police Department has
responded to the increasing gang problem by conducting dragnets
that has resulted in more than 1,400 arrests.
