<HEAD>Bullfighter in Serious Condition After Being Gored</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An assistant bullfighter was in ``very
serious'' condition Monday after being gored in the neck during a
bullfight at Madrid's annual San Isidro Festival.
   Doctors attending Antonio ``The Country Boy'' Gonzalez at
Primero de Octubre Hospital said he was on a respirator and his
vital signs were normal.
   Gonzalez underwent surgery in the bullring infirmary to close
the six-inch wound. He need a transfusion of more than five pints
of blood.
   He was gored while trying to place a pair of ``banderillas'' _
barbed sticks used to spur the bull _ and tossed several feet into
the air.
