   The regius chairs in Greek and modern history become vacant in
fall 1989 and won't be filled for at least a year, said Anne
Lonsdale, an Oxford spokeswoman.
   She said the regius chairs _ so named because they were created
by royal command _ could remain frozen beyond 1990, depending on
