<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Hit-Run Death,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hit-And-Run Driver Killed By Second Hit-And-Run Driver</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND PARK, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who initially fled a hit-and-run
accident but then pulled over to resolve the problem was struck and
killed by another hit-and-run driver, police said.
   The dead man, was identified as Duilio Vignolo, 23, of Sunrise.
   He had been driving along Interstate 95 on Sunday when he
sideswiped a vehicle owned by Duffy Shuler, 23, of Plantation.
Vignolo fled the accident, according to a Florida Highway Patrol
report.
   Later, however, he pulled over by the side of the highway.
Shuler spotted him and pulled alongside.
   Vignolo emerged first from his car and began to walk toward
Shuler. As Shuler opened his car door, a third car slammed into the
door, then plowed into Vignolo, dragging him more than 100 feet.
   The car sped away and troopers have made no arrests in the case.
