<HEAD>Olivetti Elects AT&T's Kavner To Its Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Telephone & Telegraph Co. has
maintained a link with its Italian partner, Ing. C. Olivetti and
Co. SpA, through the election of a top AT&T executive to Olivetti's
board, the company said Monday.
   There were reports of conflict between the companies earlier
this year after they could not agree on terms for AT&T to boost its
stake in Olivetti, which stands at 22.3 percent.
   Robert M. Kavner, president of AT&T's Data Systems Group, was
elected to Olivetti's board last week, AT&T announced Monday.
   Kavner, who had been AT&T's chief financial officer, was named
last month to head the Data Systems Group on the departure of
Vittorio Cassoni, a respected computer executive who returned to
Olivetti to become managing director.
   Olivetti designs and builds AT&T's personal computers and sells
a variety of AT&T products internationally, mainly in Europe.
